Create an IP Blocking Rule to Block Chat Visitors

Help your agents avoid troublesome customers by blocking chats from specified IP addresses.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To chat with visitors in Chat in the Salesforce console: Chat is enabled, set up, and included in a Salesforce console app

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. You can block chat requests from specified IP addresses by:

- Blocking visitors who use abusive language or send spam messages
- Blocking entire ranges of IP addresses if your org receives spam chats from a particular region

Blocked visitors see a message indicating that chat isnâ€™t available.

You can modify or delete blocking rules from Setup. For guidelines on entering valid IP ranges, see Set Trusted IP Ranges for Your Organization.

Agents can also block chat requests from specified IP addresses while working in the console by enabling this feature and following the instructions at Let Your Agents Block Visitors by IP Address.
title: Blocking Troublesome Chat Users with IP Rules
